programme.title: Scarlet Street (1945)
programme.desc: A lonely married man's whose only solace is painting meets a woman who thinks he is a famous artist, and they begin an affair. But he is double-crossed by his lover and her boyfriend and conned into embezzling money from his employer in order to pay for her lavish apartment.

programme.title: Murder, My Sweet (1944)
programme.desc: Adaptation of Raymond Chandler's "Farewell, My Lovely" puts hard-boiled private eye Philip Marlowe in the middle of a case involving blackmail and murder when he's hired by a hulking psychotic to find his missing girlfriend. Movie crooner Dick Powell is cast against type as Marlowe. The story was first filmed in 1942 (as "The Falcon Takes Over," with George Sanders), then was remade (as "Farewell,

programme.title: The House on Telegraph Hill (1951)
programme.desc: Concentration camp survivor Victoria Kowelska finds herself involved in mystery, greed, and murder when she assumes the identity of a dead friend in order to gain passage to America.

programme.title: Don't Bother to Knock (1952)
programme.desc: A mentally unstable woman gets a job as a babysitter at a hotel, and is on the verge of killing herself and a girl after the child discovered her canoodling with a man.

programme.title: Niagara (1953)
programme.desc: An adulterous wife purposely flaunts her sexuality to drive her jealous husband into a rage so that her lover will kill him.

programme.title: Cornered (1945)
programme.desc: A World War II veteran hunts down the Nazi collaborators who killed his wife.

programme.title: Born to Kill (1947)
programme.desc: Ruthless film noir about a psychotic murderer involved with amorous sisters. Stylishly directed.

programme.title: Dangerous Crossing (1953)
programme.desc: Moderate thriller about a bridegroom who disappears on an ocean voyage. Jeanne Crain, Carl Betz, Michael Rennie, Casey Adams, Mary Anderson. Directed by Joseph H. Newman.

programme.title: Tension (1949)
programme.desc: Film-noir suspense tale about a timid, cuckolded pharmacist who undertakes a methodical plan to murder his wife's lover, but when someone beats him to it, the husband becomes the prime suspect.

programme.title: Leave Her to Heaven (1945)
programme.desc: An insanely jealous wife sabotages everything in her husband's life until he finally leaves her. Despondent and more crazed than ever, she devises the ultimate revenge and vows to enact it no matter what sacrifice it requires of her. Gene Tierney was nominated for Best Actress as the wife.

programme.title: The Culpepper Cattle Co. (1972)
programme.desc: Yarn about a greenhorn (Gary Grimes) whose first cattle drive is beset by a stampede, rustlers and horse thieves. Frank: Billy Green Bush. Luke: Luke Askew. Dixie: Bo Hopkins. Russ: Geoffrey Lewis. Missoula: Wayne Sutherlin. Pierce: John McLiam. Pete: Matt Clark. Filmed on location in Sonora, Mexico, and Santa Fe, N.M. Directed by Dick Richards.

programme.title: Broken Arrow (1950)
programme.desc: A frontiersman tries make peace between white settlers and Apaches.

programme.title: Ghost of Sierra de Cobra (1964)
programme.desc: A blind man is plagued by ghostly phone calls. Martin Landau. Housekeeper: Judith Anderson. Mrs. Mandore: Diane Baker.

programme.title: The Ghost and Mrs. Muir (1947)
programme.desc: Despite warnings from a realtor, a young widow buys a cottage on the English coast that is said to be haunted by the previous owner: a sea captain, of whose spirit she becomes very fond.

programme.title: I Married a Witch (1942)
programme.desc: The spirit of a 17th century sorceress rematerializes in 1942 New England and falls head over heels in love with a young, handsome politician.

programme.title: Bell Book and Candle (1958)
programme.desc: A Manhattan witch falls in love with a publisher after casting a spell on him that obliges him to dump his fiancée and pursue her instead.

programme.title: Blithe Spirit (1945)
programme.desc: David Lean directed Noel Coward's fantasy about a ghost returning to disrupt her husband's second marriage.

programme.title: Electric Dreams (1984)
programme.desc: A love triangle is constructed when an architect buys a computer with emotional proclivities and they vie for the same girl. Lenny Von Dohlen, Virginia Madsen. Bill: Maxwell Caulfield. Edgar: Bud Cort. Ryley: Don Fellows. Frank: Alan Polonsky. Clerk: Wendy Miller. Directed by Steve Barron.

programme.title: Domestic Disturbance (2001)
programme.desc: A divorced boat builder discovers that his young son's stepdad is masking an evil side, forcing him to desperately try to protect his ex-wife and son from the new man in their lives.

programme.title: Perry Mason: The Case of the Murdered Madam (1987)
programme.desc: Mason (Raymond Burr) uncovers fraud while investigating the murder of a former madam (Ann Jillian). Della: Barbara Hale. Paul: William Katt. Miranda: Daphne Ashbrook. Leonard: James Noble. Richard: Bill Macy. Edward: John Rhys-Davies. Steve: Anthony Geary. Michael: David Ogden Stiers. Directed by Ron Satlof.

programme.title: Pretty Poison (1968)
programme.desc: Tale of madness and murder, filmed in Great Barrington, Mass. Anthony Perkins, Tuesday Weld. Mrs. Stepanek: Beverly Garland. Azenauer: John Randolph. Bud: Dick O'Neill. Mrs. Bronson: Clarice Blackburn. Pete: Joseph Bova. Harry: Ken Kercheval. Watchman: Parker Fennelly. Noel Black directed.

programme.title: Dracula's Widow (1988)
programme.desc: Sylvia Kristel as a venomous vamp stalking L.A.. Lannon: Josef Sommer. Everett: Lenny Von Dohlen. Brad: Marc Coppola. Helsing: Stefan Schnabel. Jenny: Rachel Jones.

programme.title: The Oregon Trail (1959)
programme.desc: A reporter (Fred MacMurray) accompanies a wagon train to Oregon in 1846. Wayne: William Bishop. Seton: Henry Hull. Prudence: Nina Shipman. Shona: Gloria Talbott. Gene Fowler Jr. directed.

programme.title: The Long Voyage Home (1940)
programme.desc: The lives of the crew who live aboard the freighter Glencairn are followed as they drink, womanize, fight and bond, sometimes searching for ways to cure boredom, and sometimes facing life or death situations.

programme.title: Blondie (1938)
programme.desc: Blondie's husband, Dagwood, gets into financial misadventures at home and in the office on the eve of their fifth wedding anniversary. Blondie helps her feckless husband get everything back. First entry in the popular family series based on the comic strip created by Chic Young.

programme.title: Sherlock Holmes Faces Death (1943)
programme.desc: A chessboard is a key to murders at the Musgrave estate. Basil Rathbone, Nigel Bruce, Hillary Brooke. Vickery: Milburn Stone. Sexton: Arthur Margetson. Philip: Gavin Muir. Brunton: Halliwell Hobbes. Lestrade: Dennis Hoey. Standard. Roy William Neill directed.

programme.title: Fractured Flickers
programme.desc: Fractured Flickers is a live-action syndicated half-hour television comedy show that was produced by Jay Ward, who is otherwise known for animated cartoons. The pilot film was produced in 1961, but the series wasn't completed until 1963. Twenty-six episodes were produced; they were syndicated by Desilu Productions and played for several years on local stations.

programme.title: The Young Indiana Jones Chronicles
programme.desc: The youthful adventures of the 'Raiders of the Lost Ark' hero, as recalled by Indy at age 93.

programme.title: Gargoyles (1972)
programme.desc: Horror fantasy about creatures planning to wipe out mankind. Cornel Wilde, Jennifer Salt. Head Gargoyle: Bernie Casey. Mrs. Parks: Grayson Hall. Reeger: Scott Glenn. Uncle Willie: Woodrow Chambliss. Police Chief: William Stevens. Partly filmed in Carlsbad Caverns, N.M. Directed by B.W.L. Norton.

programme.title: The Alligator People (1959)
programme.desc: Tale of a doctor who can turn people into monstrous creatures. Lorimer: Bruce Bennett. Sinclair: George Macready. Jane: Beverly Garland. Mrs. Hawthorne: Frieda Inescort. Mannon: Lon Chaney. Some chilling moments.

programme.title: The Fly (1958)
programme.desc: A scientist mutates into a grotesque fly creature after a teleportation experiment goes awry.

programme.title: Return of the Fly (1959)
programme.desc: Some good special effects highlight this sequel to "The Fly." Vincent Price, Brett Halsey. Alan: David Frankham. Inspector: John Sutton. Cecile: Danielle De Metz. Max: Dan Seymour. Edward Bernds directed.

programme.title: Three Coins in the Fountain (1954)
programme.desc: Oscars went to Milton Krasner's location photography and to the title song of this romance about three young American women looking for love in Italy. A Best Picture nominee.
